wikipedia_page.main: William West Sr. FLS (22 February 1848 in Leeds – 14 May 1914 in Bradford) was an English botanist, particularly noted for his studies of freshwater algae.  He had sons named William (1875–1901) and George Stephen (1876–1919), both also botanists.
